97497496b888a10f494fc7" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <strong>Bluetooth:</strong> 5.0<br> <strong>Battery life:</strong> Up to 20 hours<br> <strong>IP Rating:</strong> IPX2<br> <strong>Aux inputs:</strong> 3.5mm<br> <strong>Frequency range:</strong> 40Hz - 20kHz<br> <strong>App:</strong> No</p><p> If you didn&#39;t know about Marshall&#39;s history in amplifiers and rock music, the design should clue you in. The <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAbo_J-etV12iBUMEXMg9O3ytZzhC3SAk-LnKuNV-o_d6&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FMarshall-Tufton-Portable-Bluetooth-Speaker%2Fdp%2FB07QJD5MT4">Tufton</a> is the largest <em>portable</em> Bluetooth speaker from the company, looking much like an amp itself (as do most of them). It has physical knobs at the top and a carry strap to help move it about. While it may appear as rugged as concert gear, it&#39;s less impervious to the elements as some with just an IPX2 rating, so it&#39;s protected from light splashes from above.</p><p> Whether or not you&#39;re a fan of the brand, the rich and distinctly thumping output may make you one. We felt pulled into the sound while listening to the Tufton, a bit more than most other speakers we tested at this scale. It&#39;s dynamic, warm and, dare we say, analog in its audio presence. It&#39;s also multi-directional with a supplemental driver on the back along with a bass port.</p><p> There&#39;s no app to adjust the EQ, just the physical controls including a Bluetooth connect button, a power/volume knob and two for bass and treble. Once powered on, you can use the volume knob to set a max headroom and adjust volume on the fly from your source. The bass and treble knobs help you choose the tone of your adventure, from a purely flat soundscape to an enhanced one. We just wish you could see the dial indicators in the dark. Other features include aptX support and quick-charge capabilities that provide four hours of listening time in just 20 minutes, plus great standby battery life.</p><h2> <strong>Price: $450 and higher</strong></h2><h3> JBL Boombox 3 ($500)</h3><p><core-commerce id="3d53d17f1472443d9fdf4fa5bd99dc6a" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <strong>Bluetooth:</strong> 5.3<br> <strong>Battery life:</strong> Up to 24 hours<br> <strong>IP Rating:</strong> IPX7<br> <strong>Aux inputs:</strong> 3.5mm<br> <strong>Frequency range:</strong> 40Hz - 20kHz<br> <strong>App:</strong> Yes</p><p> If you&#39;re a fan of JBL&#39;s smaller portables, but want to kick the volume up several degrees higher, the <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ncC9wcm9kdWN0L0IwOVlEUzhCSEs_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZngtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjFiZDNhMGJkLTdjYTEtNDU0Yi1iNGNkLTNhZmE1NWQ1MTg1MCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAZpZJ5RN0EU4dauV-xJCkqxuAuWxZlqA1jluZeUyCyf5&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09YDS8BHK">Boombox 3</a> is a good choice. This 160-watt-plus big brother to the Xtreme 3 provides that familiar JBL sound but, you know, louder. The output has bright and dynamic highs and floor shaking sub-bass that may benefit more from an indoor environment with surfaces to bounce off. It doesn&#39;t have the long throw that “loudspeakers” have, although to be clear, it is pretty loud. This is a dance party tool for your basement rumpus room, garage hangout, beach or poolside craziness.</p><p> The Boombox 3 has a few upgrades from the previous gen. The exterior looks mostly the same, but it&#39;s now IP67 rated making it very rugged. It&#39;s also a touch heavier at 14.7 pounds, possibly since this device now has a woofer alongside the mids and tweeters.</p><p> It&#39;s still a convenient grab-and-go speaker for most occasions when you want the music to be the star of the show (or at least not disappear into the background). The battery can keep you playing for up to 24 hours, but it also runs at full volume while plugged in. In fact, while it&#39;s connected to an outlet, the total output wattage gets a boost from 160 watts to 180 watts.</p><h3> Sony SRS-XP700 (~$398)</h3><p><core-commerce id="cd16262743454b4ca679d1e717af5cee" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <strong>Bluetooth:</strong> 5.0<br> <strong>Battery life:</strong> Up to 20 hours<br> <strong>IP Rating:</strong> IPX4<br> <strong>Aux inputs:</strong> 3.5mm, USB thumb drive listening, Guitar, Mic<br> <strong>Frequency range:</strong> N/A<br> <strong>App:</strong> Yes</p><p> Sony&#39;s big <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdy6iMeOziUFDec3PsldvU2pdcJfYoVrxHmthKZk8dHR&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSony-Portable-Bluetooth-Karaoke-Party-Speaker-Splash-Resistant-Hour-Battery%2Fdp%2FB094T99V63">SRS-XP700 Bluetooth speaker</a> is a good party speaker for fans of loud, thumping beats. The unit has the look of a futuristic stereo speaker at 2.25 feet tall and about 37 pounds, with pleasing lighting effects on the inside of both top and bottom grab bars. You&#39;ll also find USB charging ports and LDAC support, while the app offers customization including light controls.</p><p> The XP700 remains portable enough for many people to shuffle around locally without <em>too</em> much effort and its IPX4 rating means it can handle spills and splashes. The exterior is hard plastic with some rubberized feet, but it&#39;s not the type of speaker you want to treat carelessly. It&#39;s mostly a homebody that can fire up parties in lofts, garages, basements or backyards. You can also wirelessly pair two for a more powerful experience.</p><p> While the sound is big and bassy, it comes up short on handling the lowest registers well. Also, the high end isn&#39;t as pronounced as it could be, so it may not be for everyone. It&#39;s more of a loudspeaker style, so it&#39;s better in bigger rooms and shines at louder volumes.</p><h3> Soundboks Go ($699)</h3><p><core-commerce id="a0731d1938ed48e3ada7e9b7392dcdc8" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <strong>Bluetooth:</strong> 5.0<br> <strong>Battery life:</strong> Up to 40 hours<br> <strong>IP Rating:</strong> IP65<br> <strong>Aux inputs:</strong> 3.5mm<br> <strong>Frequency range:</strong> 40Hz - 20kHz<br> <strong>App:</strong> Yes</p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ncC9wcm9kdWN0L0IwOVlSTVJHS1Y_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZngtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjFiZDNhMGJkLTdjYTEtNDU0Yi1iNGNkLTNhZmE1NWQ1MTg1MCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAVR6IRJRQbNa62mA9zIUHt7c2_oKphMrHKHo9U5-R4d1&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09YRMRGKV">Soundboks Go</a> is a top performer if you&#39;re looking for a portable Bluetooth option that provides a big sound for larger spaces, although it comes at a price. This unpretentious black rectangle is half the size of its more professional sibling the Soundboks Gen 3. It packs one 10-inch woofer and a 1-inch domed tweeter, both powered by two 72W RMS amps for massive sound and chunky bass, even at a distance.</p><p> At 20 pounds, this party speaker is fairly easy to lug around and looks about the size of carry-on luggage. You can even get the optional shoulder strap, which helps for longer missions. It has a flexible TPE handle on top, silicone bumpers around the edges and ABS+Polycarbonate exterior and grill. The IP65 rating also marks it as a resilient device in most environments.</p><p> The sound makes a big statement here. Output levels are rated at up to 121dB, with clear mids and highs projecting clearly across large areas. The low end also has a significant presence at a distance, matching up with 40Hz frequency response. It&#39;s definitely capable enough to support large gatherings.</p><p> The speaker is easy to connect to via Bluetooth and the partner app offers EQ customization, audio profiles and OTA firmware updates. There&#39;s a solitary 3.5mm stereo input on the Go, but its wireless expansion shines, letting you connect up to five Soundboks Gen 3 or Go speakers at the touch of a button with its built-in SKAA wireless support.</p><p> Lastly, the battery pack is removable, swappable and also long-lasting for a speaker this size; at low to mid volume, it&#39;s rated at up to 40 hours runtime. For transparency, Soundboks also lets you know to expect around 10 hours of play at full volume. You <em>can</em> also run this while charging, but there are strict warnings about keeping the volume low while doing so (it&#39;s not recommended unless you&#39;re desperate).</p><h2>常见问题解答</h2><h3>How does a Bluetooth speaker work?</h3><p> Bluetooth technology lets devices connect and exchange data over short distances using ultra high frequency (UHF) radio waves. It&#39;s the frequency range that&#39;s carved out for industrial, scientific and medical purposes, called the 2.4GHz ISM spectrum band. This range is available worldwide, making it easy for companies to use with devices for global markets.</p><p> Bluetooth speakers include this tech, which lets them communicate with source devices like smartphones, tablets or computers in order to exchange data. The two devices pair by sharing a unique code and will work within the proscribed range for the device and Bluetooth version.</p><p> Ever since Bluetooth 4.0 was released over a decade ago, new iterations usually improve on range, use less power and offer expanded connectivity with features like multipoint (allowing more than one device to be connected at the same time, for instance).</p><h3> Who should buy a Portable Bluetooth speaker?</h3><p> If you want to play music while you&#39;re out-and-about on something other than headphones, a portable Bluetooth speaker is probably what you want. There&#39;s a broad range of devices for all types of circumstances. Many adventurous people will want a relatively lightweight portable that&#39;s rugged enough to handle the elements while also packing enough charge to play for hours on end. Others may simply need a speaker they can move around the house or use in the backyard. In this case, you can choose larger less rugged models that may offer better sound.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-portable-bluetooth-speakers-133004551.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-portable-bluetooth-speakers-133004551.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 1bd3a0bd-7ca1-454b-b4cd-3afa55d51850</guid><dc:creator> Jon Turi</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jul 2023 12:08:06 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689941287</ingested><modified> 2023-07-21T12:08:22+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Speakers & Headphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Turi]]></category><media:content height="1615" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-04/85e08920-b759-11ec-beb9-015235c0a851" width="2500"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1615" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-04/85e08920-b759-11ec-beb9-015235c0a851" width="2500"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Jon Turi / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A group of portable Bluetooth speakers in front of a shelf full of books and stuff.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Portable Bluetooth speakers]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Morning After: What to expect at Samsung’s Unpacked 2023 event next week]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>随着竞争最终开始解决可折叠产品，三星准备证明它仍然可以提供最好的产品。其下一场 Unpacked 活动将展示新一代可折叠手机，旁边还有智能手表和平板电脑。这就是<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/summer-samsung-unpacked-2023-what-to-expect-on-july-26th-150001571.html">我们所期待的。</a></p><p>虽然尚未命名新硬件，但该公司预计将发布 Galaxy Z Flip 5 和 Galaxy Z Fold 5。不过，今年的优先顺序颠倒了。书本式的 Fold 通常是主要吸引力，但今年 Flip 翻盖可能会受到最多的关注，它的正面屏幕大幅扩大，可以与<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/moto-razr-review-finally-some-real-competition-for-samsungs-flip-foldables-203033514.html#:~:text=The%20Moto%20Razr%2B%2C%20a%20foldable,widgets%20that%20you%20can%20use."><ins>摩托罗拉 Razr+</ins></a>等竞争对手抗衡。 Galaxy Z Flip 5和Galaxy Z Fold 5都可能采用“水滴”铰链，在关闭时缩小间隙。我们为什么要关心？它将是一个更纤薄的可折叠设备，并且在设备关闭时具有更小的间隙。</p> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/summer-samsung-unpacked-2023-what-to-expect-on-july-26th-150001571.html"><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/dd68c010-27a9-11ee-96dd-8d435a09fb78" style="height:450px;width:675px;" alt="TMA" data-uuid="bbb0cc7a-97b8-3837-b183-a39be971d5a2"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">泄密事件</div></figure></a><p>在可穿戴设备方面，该公司毫不隐晦地暗示 Galaxy Watch 6 将出现在 Unpacked 展会上，有报道甚至暗示经典版或专业版将带回物理旋转表圈。 （有些人沉迷于带有旋转边框的智能手表。）</p><p>三星最新的高端 Android 手机 Galaxy Tab S9 将会是我们的预测的最后一环。我们期待看到这款笔记本电脑的基础版、增强版和超级版，配备升级的屏幕，甚至可能具有 IP67 防尘防水功能。</p><p>三星将于美国东部时间 26 日上午 7 点开始在其<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.youtube.com/samsung"><ins>YouTube 频道</ins></a>上直播此次活动。如果您想睡个懒觉，请不要担心——我们将在博客中进行直播，并希望能够亲身体验这些新设备。敬请关注。</p><p> ——马特·史密斯</p><p></p><h3>您可能错过的最重要的故事</h3><h3></h3><p><a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-is-bringing-its-palm-based-payments-to-all-whole-foods-market-stores-132413042.html"><ins>亚马逊正在向所有 Whole Foods Market 商店推出基于掌上支付的支付方式</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-makes-it-easier-to-send-messages-to-unsaved-numbers-093511724.html"><ins>WhatsApp 让您可以更轻松地向未保存的号码发送消息</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/star-trek-strange-new-worlds-finds-empathy-in-memory-130048301.html"><ins>《星际迷航：奇异新世界》在记忆中找到同理心</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apples-macbook-air-m1-is-back-on-sale-for-750-160059819.html"><ins>Apple MacBook Air M1 重新发售，售价 750 美元</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/adult-swim-lands-new-show-from-cowboy-bebop-and-john-wick-creators-161557849.html"><ins>Adult Swim 推出由《星际牛仔》和《疾速追杀》创作者创作的新节目</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-multi-device-wireless-chargers-130020900.html"><ins>2023 年最佳多设备无线充电器</ins></a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-wireless-workout-headphones-191517835.html"><ins>2023 年最佳无线健身耳机</ins></a></p><p></p><h2><a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/kevin-mitnick-formerly-the-worlds-most-wanted-hacker-has-passed-away-084912966.html">前世界头号通缉黑客凯文·米特尼克去世</a></h2><h3>米特尼克出狱后成为白帽黑客和网络安全顾问。</h3><h3></h3><p>曾经的世界头号通缉电脑黑客凯文·米特尼克 (Kevin Mitnick) 于 7 月 16 日去世，享年 59 岁。米特尼克第一次渗透计算机系统是在 1979 年，但直到 1988 年他才被定罪，当时他因复制公司软件而被判处 12 个月监禁。他在被监管释放期间侵入了 Pacific Bell 的语音邮件计算机，并在 90 年代作为逃犯继续侵入手机网络以及公司和政府网站。</p><p>米特尼克还参与了数千份文件和信用卡号码的盗窃活动，但他的讣告称，他“从未从任何‘受害者’那里拿过一毛钱。”米特尼克最终在监狱里度过了五年，出狱时他称这是一次“假期”。从那时起，他改变了自己的职业生涯，成为了一名白帽黑客和网络安全顾问。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/kevin-mitnick-formerly-the-worlds-most-wanted-hacker-has-passed-away-084912966.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></p><p></p><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/youtube-premium-quietly-goes-up-in-price-to-14-per-month-100531473.html https://www.engadget.com/...">YouTube Premium 悄然涨至每月 14 美元</a></h2><h3>在没有正式宣布的情况下，这一金额大幅增加了 2 美元。</h3><h3></h3><p>我昨天已经暗示过这一点，但这里有更详细的细节。 YouTube Premium 价格大幅上涨 2 美元，从 12 美元增至 14 美元，年费从每月 120 美元增至 140 美元，比按月付费节省了约 28 美元。去年，谷歌将家庭高级套餐提高到每月 23 美元，并向现有的按月订阅用户收取新费用。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/youtube-premium-quietly-goes-up-in-price-to-14-per-month-100531473.html https://www.engadget.com/..."><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></p><p></p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-is-reportedly-testing-an-ai-tool-that-can-generate-news-articles-054602544.html">据报道，谷歌正在测试人工智能工具来生成新闻文章</a></h2><h3>这家科技巨头已将其推荐给《纽约时报》和其他出版物。</h3> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/google-is-reportedly-testing-an-ai-tool-that-can-generate-news-articles-054602544.html"><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/98e9a7b0-27a9-11ee-af6a-25f40a92a0c4" style="height:450px;width:675px;" alt="TMA" data-uuid="1c9fa35b-1ac0-373b-a44e-f7661f42d525"><figcaption></figcaption> <div class="photo-credit">400tmax 来自 Getty Images</div></figure></a><p>据<em>《纽约时报》</em>报道，谷歌正在测试一项代号为 Genesis 的新 AI 技术，该技术可以生成新闻文章。据报道，这家科技巨头已向<em>《泰晤士报》</em>以及<em>《华盛顿邮报</em>》和拥有<em>《华尔街日报》</em>的新闻集团的高管展示了该工具。根据现场见证者的报告，Genesis 可以从输入的数据中提取副本，无论是时事还是其他类型的信息。谷歌相信记者可以将其用作自动化任务的助手，并让他们腾出时间去做其他事情。一些记者担心这很可能会让他们失业。</p><p>但机器人还没有完全做到这一点： <em>CNET</em>在发现其在<em>CNET Money</em>署名下发布的 77 篇机器撰写文章中的大部分存在重大错误后， <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/cnet-corrected-41-of-its-77-ai-written-articles-201519489.html"><ins>不得不进行更正</ins></a>。就在本月早些时候， <em>Gizmodo 的 io9</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://variety.com/2023/digital/news/io9-ai-generated-star-wars-article-errors-1235662194/"><ins>发表了</ins></a>一篇《星球大战》文章，其中充满了 Gizmodo 机器人造成的错误。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-is-reportedly-testing-an-ai-tool-that-can-generate-news-articles-054602544.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></p><p></p><p></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-what-to-expect-at-samsungs-unpacked-2023-event-next-week-111516314.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-what-to-expect-at-samsungs-unpacked-2023-event-next-week-111516314.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 1001d5c5-9826-427c-ae5b-f49d00495acb</guid><dc:creator>马特·史密斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jul 2023 11:15:16 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689933480</ingested><modified> 2023-07-21T09:58:13+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mat Smith]]></category>