TA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="1664" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-11/75dba370-65c3-11ed-bafa-0913efd55e54" width="2812"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1664" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-11/75dba370-65c3-11ed-bafa-0913efd55e54" width="2812"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[James Trew / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The GoPro Hero 11 Black Mini pictured on a rocky surface in a park with roman-style columns and palm trees in the background.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[GoPro Hero 11 Black Mini]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Seven AI companies commit to safeguards at the White House's request]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>在<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/statements-releases/2023/07/21/fact-sheet-biden-harris-administration-secures-voluntary-commitments-from-leading-artificial-intelligence-companies-to-manage-the-risks-posed-by-ai/">白宫的推动</a>下，<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/microsoft/">微软</a>、<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/google/">谷歌</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/openai/">OpenAI</a>等美国人工智能领域的领导者已承诺为其技术提供一定的保障。这些公司将自愿同意遵守多项原则，但该协议将在国会通过监管人工智能的立法时到期。</p><p>拜登政府将<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/white-house-reveals-its-next-steps-towards-responsible-ai-development-190636857.html">重点放在</a>确保人工智能公司<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/white-house-unveils-its-blueprint-for-an-ai-bill-of-rights-175912494.html">负责任地开发技术上</a>。官员们希望确保科技公司能够以造福社会的方式在生成式人工智能领域进行创新，同时又不会对公众的安全、权利和民主价值观产生负面影响。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>今年 5 月，副总裁卡玛拉·哈里斯 (Kamala Harris) <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/vice-president-harris-tells-tech-ceos-they-have-a-moral-responsibility-to-safeguard-ai-211049047.html">会见了</a>OpenAI、微软、Alphabet 和 Anthropic 的首席执行官，并告诉他们有责任确保他们的人工智能产品安全可靠。上个月，乔·拜登总统会见了该领域的领导人， <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/president-biden-meets-with-ai-tech-leaders-in-san-francisco-182140363.html">讨论人工智能问题</a>。</p><p>科技公司已就有关安全、安保和社会责任的八项建议措施达成一致。其中包括：</p><ul><li><p>让独立专家测试模型是否存在不良行为</p></li><li><p>投资网络安全</p></li><li><p>鼓励第三方发现安全漏洞</p></li><li><p>标记社会风险，包括偏见和不当使用</p></li><li><p>重点研究人工智能的社会风险</p></li><li><p>与其他公司和政府共享信任和安全信息</p></li><li><p>对音频和视频内容加水印，以帮助明确内容是人工智能生成的</p></li><li><p>使用被称为前沿模型的最先进的人工智能系统来解决社会最严重的问题</p></li></ul><p>&quot;These commitments, which the companies have chosen to undertake immediately, underscore three principles that must be fundamental to the future of AI — safety, security, and trust — and mark a critical step toward developing responsible AI,&quot; the White House statement read. “随着创新步伐不断加快，拜登-哈里斯政府将继续提醒这些公司他们的责任，并采取果断行动来确保美国人的安全。”</p><p>这是一项自愿协议，这一事实凸显了立法者跟上人工智能发展步伐的难度。国会已提出多项法案，希望对人工智能进行监管。其中一项旨在阻止公司利用<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-01-31-s230-repeal.html">第 230 条保护措施</a>来<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/senate-bill-would-hold-ai-companies-liable-for-harmful-content-212340911.html">避免对人工智能生成的有害内容承担责任</a>，而另一项则旨在要求<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/republicans-attack-biden-with-a-fully-ai-generated-ad-184055192.html">政治广告</a>在使用生成式人工智能时<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/house-bill-would-demand-disclosure-of-ai-generated-content-in-political-ads-190524733.html">包含披露内容</a>。 Of note, administrators in the House of Representatives have reportedly <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/congress-is-reportedly-limiting-staff-use-of-ai-models-like-chatgpt-195454777.html">placed limits</a> on the use of generative AI in congressional offices.</p><p> <strong>Update 7/21 5:47AM</strong> : This article has been updated to include a statement from the White House.</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/ai-companies-will-reportedly-commit-to-safeguards-at-the-white-houses-request-185646283.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/ai-companies-will-reportedly-commit-to-safeguards-at-the-white-houses-request-185646283.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8ef25295-4cd3-4385-89b7-deee6fee5192</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jul 2023 09:47:58 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689946057</ingested><modified> 2023-07-21T13:27:41+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="3648" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/d2269490-103c-11ee-9f34-f3e35a1c5052" width="5200"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3648" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/d2269490-103c-11ee-9f34-f3e35a1c5052" width="5